DataElement.preferredName: Clinical Trial Eligibility Criteria Other Therapeutic Procedure Begin Year Checkbox Indicator
DataElement.preferredDefinition: Indicator to determine other treatment start year for questions that are necessary to allow a person to participate in a clinical study, as outlined in the study protocol.

DataElementConcept.preferredName: Clinical Trial Eligibility Criteria Other Therapeutic Procedure Begin Year
DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: Characteristics which are necessary to allow a subject to participate in a clinical study, as outlined in the study protocol. The concept covers inclusion and exclusion criteria._Different than the one(s) previously specified or mentioned._An action or administration of therapeutic agents to produce an effect that is intended to alter or stop a pathologic process._Have a beginning, in a temporal, spatial, or evaluative sense; the point in space or time where something begins._A period of time that it takes for Earth to make a complete revolution around the sun, approximately 365 days; a specific one year period.
